    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-23T04:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-23T04:00:00-05:00" n="417"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d417">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/4–2346: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Mukden</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mukden</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-23T17:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 23, 1946—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 24—7 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>47. About 40 Chinese officials most of whom were Central Govt. arrived here in 2
                    Chinese planes from Harbin on 20th, another group arrived today and it is
                    rumored more are coming. They will reputedly stay for present at Mukden.</p>
                <p>Please repeat Nanking.</p>
                <p>Movement presumably connected with Chinese belief that Harbin will go way of
                    Changchun after withdrawal Soviet troops scheduled for noon tomorrow.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
